{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect UE filtering in eNB tracer GUI\n\n### Summary\nThe eNB tracer GUI was not displaying UE-specific information correctly when switching between UEs. This happened because the code was initializing the current UE to ID 3, but this UE ID was not yet assigned to any RNTI at startup. As a result, all the filters were set to match events for UE ID 3, but no RNTI had been assigned that ID yet, so no events would display.\n\nThis fix changes the initialization to use UE ID 0, which is pre-assigned to RNTI 65535 after reset_ue_ids(), ensuring that the filters can match actual events.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/enb.c`: Changed initialization from `enb_data.ue = 3` to `enb_data.ue = 0` \n- `common/utils/T/tracer/enb.c`: Added protection against negative UE IDs in `set_current_ue` function\n\nWhen running the eNB tracer with a database file, previously no UE data would display when first opening the GUI. Now the GUI correctly shows data for UE ID 0 (mapped to RNTI 65535) on startup.\n"
}